Apple’s upcoming event on 27 March may see the unveiling of cheaper iPads and MacBook Air. According to a report by Softpedia, the event – Let’s Take a Field Trip – is rumoured to focus on the education sector. The cheaper iPad and MacBook Air devices will be aimed at classroom use, stated the report. “One of the new products that Apple could announce is a new iPad, a cheaper model with a 9.7-inch display and probably Face ID authentication,” it said. The event is also rumoured to host the official release of iOS 11.3, which includes new AR experiences, Business Chat for companies, and a Health Records feature. The event will start at 17:00 SA time on 27 March.